text: Dabataw, United States National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency is a village in Ye Township in Mawlamyine District in the Mon State of south-east Burma (Myanmar). Dabataw is on a tributary of the Palantha Chaung, in the foothills of the Tenasserim Range, about east of Waipathe.Burma 1:250,000 topographic map, Series U542, ND 47-02 Ye U.S. Army Map Service, December 1959 ==Notes== ==External links== * "Dabataw Map — Satellite Images of Dabataw" Maplandia World Gazetteer Category:Populated places in Mon State
